        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:14PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 314 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Organ, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands Missile Range Main Post, Dona Ana, Organ, Talavera, East
Mesa, Northeast Las Cruces, Dripping Springs, Aguirre Springs,
Portions of Organ Mountains Desert Peaks National Monument, Soledad
Canyon, and San Augustin Pass.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 25 in New Mexico near mile marker 1.
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 153 and 172.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
